description.en: The Machine Learning Test Ontology was built to characterize failures that have been identified during the use of machine learning tools, in particular the TensorFlow tool.

comments.en: An ontology to describe the testing process in Machine Learning tools to describe how failures occur in these systems. Created by Alexandre Locci Martins and Ana Cristina Vierira de Melo.

comment.undefined: "TensorFlow is an open-source platform developed by Google for the purpose of machine learning and deep learning. It is widely used to develop and train machine learning models."
Applications that support and accelerate TensorFlow workflows.
Jupyter Notebook environment that is not necessary be setting and runs in the cloud.

The goal of TensorFlow Model Analysis is to provide a mechanism for model evaluation in TFX. TensorFlow Model Analysis allows to perform model evaluations in the TFX pipeline, and view resultant metrics and plots in a Jupyter notebook.
